caption: This is a chill burger and wings spot with a nice compliment of beers on tap and bottle. Their signature spice rub (an absolute must try) made this the best seasoned burger I've ever had. Absolutely delicious!!
Bonnie’s grill makes some of the best mild Buffalo wings.  When I am in Brooklyn near the Barclay center or just passing through I have to snag an order.

Cool staff cool Management !! & Probably the only place on 5th you could get a real milkshake, a delicious burger and some bomb wings.  The Western Burger is my favorite by the way :) just place your order already ! :D
Amazing food the nachos are awesome and don’t forget to ask about the secret menu.
Food is great! Lunch special of $10 can't be beat!
A perfectly cooked and seasoned burger, the most delicious fries and onion rings and the nicest service! An excellent Park Slope treasure! Thank you for making me feel right at home
Delicious wings !!

I love Bonnie’s Grill! My friend took me here about 8 years ago when I first moved to Brooklyn and until these days this is my to go spot for burgers and wings in BK. I went there last week and they had the best IPA on tap. After you go Bonnie’s you never go back!
Cute place with an oldschool diner vibe.  Buffalo Bills Backer bar with amazing food.  Recommend the Bonnie's Burger.  Side salad is a legit salad, not just iceburg.

I sent my friends to this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I visit this place often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The dishes they serve are delicious and the crew is efficient and cooperative. Whenever we visit this place we pass a pleasing time.  I recommend this place with pleasure.
The fries & onion rings were so nice & crispy, even after some time after being served. The turkey burger had nice spices in there. I also had the cookies & cream milkshake & it was yummy.

It was our first time here and I must say, we were impressed. We were able to sit indoors and the burgers were amazing! So worth what we paid. I really wish I would have taken pictures but we were all busy stuffing our faces with these huge burgers! We will definitely be back.

Bonnie’s sets the bar in terms of wing quality. This place was our go-to in Brooklyn. Now that I’m in Los Angeles and scouting for new wing spots, we’re always comparing to Bonnie’s... and have found no such match.  Crispy, saucy, juicy, and big. Look no further for great wings in Brooklyn.
Best wings in Park Slope (maybe Brooklyn?)! Friendly staff and great service. Plus it’s a Bills Bar!
Food has no flavor and beyond trash. “ it’s a “whited up” no seasons place of burgers and fries. Wings you could tell were heated up from a bag. Worst money spent on food. Do not recommend!

This is definitely a staple in park slope.The burgers and wings are definitely quality. The food always comes out fast. And Flo’s service is always on point. Wish I had pictures but I never get a shot because I'm always too busy digging in!

Food here is always good, especially their burgers; giant and taste great. Milkshakes are also really delicious. Their philly cheesesteak and wings are also really good! Spicy coleslaw is excellent as well. Pricing is reasonable for the quality you get.  Staff is very friendly and speed of service is good. Would definitely recommend without hesitation, you won't be disappointed.

Bonnie’s is the best! My first child is practically made of their food. They work their tails off. And have been working the entire pandemic to make sure that everyone’s getting some good old fashion comfort food. This is a great spot. And they work extremely hard. I always look forward to a great meal at Bonnie’s. You can get salads you can get wings you can get burgers! And the sides are fantastic. Wish they were Jets fans but you can’t have it all!

I give starts only for the good server and here is why I think this place is not recommended: 1. My first time cold burger buns which feel like just out fridge 2. Way over priced: 2 person no drink 70+( including one regular burger, one rib, and 10 wings) 3. No sanitizer and they don’t wear gloves to serve— this is during COVID  Also this is just my experience and I just can’t understand why this place been rated so high—like 4 starts in google with this kind of food and price.

I got the corned beef hash. And tried the smoked fries too. They taste like barbeque potato chips! Everything was all around delicious. The staff was friendly and knowledgeable which won me over. Would love to go again and try some of their other menu items.

I heard about Bonnie’s after they brought food to the hospital where I work during the COVID19 pandemic. I was off that day and didn’t get a chance to try it but everyone was raving about it so I decided to give it a shot. I had mac n cheese, bbq pulled pork sandwich and oreo bread pudding. Everything was absolutely fantastic! The mac n cheese was probably the best I’ve ever had. The bread pudding was amazing! I will definitely be back. 💯

Delivery: arrived punctually! Barely warm. My burger was supposed to be medium-well but arrived charcoaled. Mac&Cheese tastes like powder-made cheese, fries were skimpy by quantity and OK by taste. Wings are 6/10. Coleslaw seems OLD and sad. Milkshake was good. Packed well. Price unjustified in my opinion.

Good

I drove by this place for 10 years.. Finally decided to stop in for lunch.. You can gamble with your time and health and come here. Maybe you'll have a decent or even a good time. It's happened before, just look at some of the other reviews. Excellent food! My first time eating their last week with my boyfriend and we both had a great meal . The serving size on the plates is more than enough  to say u get More then u pay for ! Great staff. Made us feel like regulars on our first visit. Quality food. Quick service. Wings are delish! Take the plunge and order the HOT- they are tasty. Vegetarian wings aka cauliflower were tasty too. Nice to see that on the menu. Can't wait to return and try the burger and the cheese steak.

When you search "best wings in NYC", this place tends to pop up. So of course, I had to check it out. Very relaxed atmosphere, with a ton of Buffalo fans (Bills game was on). I sat right in front of the deep fryers and the grill so I saw all the frying goodness in action. You know it's super fresh food when you can see everything the chef is doing. Major kudos to the chef - he was making a million things at once (I'm sure this is normal but how often are you arms-length away from the chef to witness all of it).  Now. The WINGS. Very good, sauce was great. I would have preferred a tad more sauce and wings could have been a bit juicer. I'm sure if the chef wasn't swamped and manning three different stations, the wings would have been pretty close to perfect.  Note: if you're a football fan, this place might not be the best place to watch a game since they only have two small tvs that are at opposite ends of the bar/restaurant. But.. if you're a Bills fan, definitely check it out & eat some wings.
